description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the established Northumberland Continuing Healthcare Nurse Assessment based at County Hall, Morpeth.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The role of the nurse assessor is to work autonomously as part of the core team delivering comprehensive assessments to determine eligibility for NHS Continuing Healthcare (CHC) and Funded Nursing Care (FNC) in accordance with the National Framework for CHC for patients in the Northumberland area.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Continuing Healthcare Nurse Assessment Team works trust-wide in partnership with health and social care colleagues to ensure multi-disciplinary working across health and social care boundaries, obtain robust evidence to support the continuing healthcare eligibility recommendation, and promote a co-ordinated approach to care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful post holder must be able to role model compassionate and inclusive leadership in order to shape the creation of a collective leadership culture within the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Essential:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered nurse with an additional qualification (either community, mental health or learning disability) and previous post registration experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered Mentor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Post Qualification teaching certificate e.g. ENB 998 or equivalent experience/ willing to complete necessary qualification.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jane Christie - Clinical Lead, Continuing Healthcare and Funded Nursing Care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jane.Christie@northumbria-healthcare.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
